id: pm-ydkl
title: pm comments/notes/learnings --add HTML-escapes angle brackets in stored text
description: "Observed 2026-05-28: passing 'pm comments pm-XXX --add \"... pm create <type> ...\"' stores the text with literal HTML entities &lt;type&gt; instead of preserving < and >. Confirmed on this session's pm-edge/pm-fl0c/pm-th6y comments. Likely a defensive escape applied at append/comment serialization; pm does not render comments as HTML so the escape is unnecessary and harms readability when agents quote shell snippets like 'pm create <type> <title>'. Investigate where the escape happens (probably in core/store/append or a sanitizer hook), and switch to either no-op or a code-fence wrap. Low priority but visible footgun."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[3]: agent-ux,fix,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-05-28T05:13:46.095Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-28T10:58:46.182Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-th6y
resolution: "Added defensive HTML-entity decode (5 core entities) at the MCP server boundary in src/mcp/server.ts:792. Decodes &lt; &gt; &quot; &#39; &amp; only when &lt; or &gt; is present in the input (no-op for normal text). Single-pass via lookup map so &amp;lt; stays as literal &lt; (preserves intentional double-encoding). Walker handles nested options/arrays. Pure helper in src/core/shared/html-entity-decode.ts with 100% test coverage."
expected_result: "pm comments/notes/learnings/create/update --add via MCP store text verbatim with literal angle brackets preserved, matching the direct-CLI behavior."
actual_result: "Verified 19 unit tests pass (idempotent, no double-decode, deep nesting, non-string passthrough). Direct CLI continues to pass &lt;type&gt; verbatim. MCP wiring in src/mcp/server.ts:792 ensures every tool-call argument tree is normalized before reaching any handler."
close_reason: Shipped defensive HTML-entity decode at MCP server boundary.
body: ""
